RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALABRIAN QUEEN was rushed to the lead to set all the pace then edged clear on the turn and drew off in the stretch. HIDDEN LOVE stalked the pace from three wide and gave late effort to be second best. FLYING I vied for the early lead then fell back on the turn and was outfinished in the stretch. JANIS chased the leaders from the inside, faded on the turn but was best of the others. TIME TO CLOSE was rank early then moved up from three wide and made a late rally in the stretch. DREAMED I AM FAST showed no early speed but improved on the inside in the stretch. SWEET N SALTY failed to menace. TENSAS CLEAR save ground to no avail. MORO DRAMA QUEEN trailed the field and was outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 30, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 30 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since September 30 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLESSED ANNA stalked the pace from three or four wide then took command at the quarter pole and drew off to prove best. DANCE LADY was off the pace on the inside on the backstretch then moved out to three wide around the final turn for a late run but was no match for the winner. PELLETIER raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn then steadily advanced down the backstretch, saved ground around the final turn but flattened out. HARLANS WARRIOR moved between horses going into the first turn then took the lead at the half mile marker and was overtaken at the quarter pole and tired. SIMPLE PLEASURE saved ground on the backstretch then moved between horses at the quarter pole to improve position. CATCAKE went to the front to take a brief early lead to the first turn then vied for the lead down the backstretch and gave way. AMERICAN REALITY was unhurried around the first turn and down the backstretch then made a five wide bid on the final turn to pass tired rivals. MISS BILLIE K was allowed to settled down the backstretch then made a rail bid on the final turn but failed to sustain that bid. CYBER SNEAKER was not a threat. COLD AS YOU prompted the pace from three wide to the first turn then retreated.

PIP SQUEEK tracked the leaders from five wide to the turn then tipped in to three wide but was no match for the winner. BACK STREET BABY broke in and bumped with inside rival at the start, trailed the field to the turn then show late effort in the stretch. RULED BY SPIRIT broke through the gate prior to the start then was forwardly placed from four wide but was through early. POINT OF VICTORY raced near the back while saving ground and passed tiring rivals. HEY MADALYN CLAIRE pressed the pace from two wide to the final turn and dropped back. MILA'S KAT floated out going into the first turn, bumped outside rival and lost action, remained back. STORM BREACH was never a threat.
